SE0Kw8E09S2nPWurd83sursg2EkJ2i58tgjHDm6LDrUN43PN4ODj16CUKIX1muEx-K4stW5J6zURM5vHD8hBwuTTu3p8DtoEHU2Cin5K_pIU-FN83arU5EloXQXMTNfFiZnW9K2vhfIe_Bzbcww8xltUfP71ZYkPLH8mBg6x1cM3kyvfglD3Dp_kY1jRlDyhBkLgTuvSqVzna_npvCJmmdU2-1yDk4P6DsYS8-p4NfMfI_wXdUJFvKKoW_i2CEnvx0pb3We3_V3d4vyZO8fyCxejM9QCJe9l99QZfG4kplYdZ5JZQ5mte5s950-FVK-M-mV1e-rnHStyShS44uAe9YTty6UgG9t0IcDayETLgqjpAmv0eGLMU4GPXPglYQyvV7DfavhYCeCJO5kOAdlm7kknwatYQm7L7fSMt38FgzZHAKB2lnxe95DsXnaZrM68G1aFncpTXURzfKCo0NKu-2NlimZ8xM-ro4brRPipzY26YED3YwFvOlCZBFhSFGaAHL9BqSImVTgVv0xLvVynfOblvMw05ss8KlKcJ_cGt2HCkpDMtkrIbG1_ACfi2wV7Zl7_teGGLgDr-Wly4VG_rDqTk5RyHU9AzHabGP04x8hGDhejSL_196Co2aX62Y0jZ33AhI6rC88LOxktBCzvHpSlnlgD4jF1SQke6u1OT2WDEn-WBTP8GvJSNqWvBz9e2gWV8_NA17VL4TiyzklwDLHitg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class unloading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how classes aren’t unloaded until the classloader is unreachable. If the TCCL holds a reference to the loader, the class remains loaded. I realize that for a class to be unloaded, the loader must be unreachable, meaning class references won’t clear if the loader is still holding them. To nullify the class reference, the loader must be unreachable, which complicates reloading with the same loader. What happens if the class name is loaded by the parent?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Managing memory allocation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using System.gc and then checking if everything is null before returning. It’s important to allocate memory wisely, without overdoing it. I could store chunks in a list, ensuring it doesn't exceed the maximum memory. The goal is to avoid problems, right? Oh, and if I catch an OutOfMemoryError, I should clear the chunks. Keeping things efficient is key to preventing memory issues in the process!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading issues**\\n\\nI’m considering how to avoid UnsupportedFeatureError by embedding bytes instead of relying on the loadClass method. I think generating class bytes might work using javax.tools at test runtime. But when dealing with ToolProvider, will it throw UnsupportedFeature? I might need to catch that Error. If it returns null, should I throw an AssertionError? If it's native, it might fail, so I could catch UnsupportedOperation as well. There’s a lot to think about here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI'm considering writing class bytes as a byte array in a test using a custom ClassLoader and the defineClass method. When it's unsupported natively, it leads to an error, but it works in the JVM. This approach for dynamic loading with \\\"generated bytecode\\\" looks promising, and I want to ensure I handle errors properly for robustness. I need to create the bytes, so I'm thinking about building an in-memory class file using DataOutputStream.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QzcoFl0yI1IDJwC1hO4XGw7H|fc_0c214f9875a02c830169f94b3c9f4481a188952942abc3dd0c", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage commons_beanutils.commons_beanutils_core;\n\nimport java.beans.IntrospectionException;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.DataOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.ref.WeakReference;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport org.apache.commons.beanutils.MappedPropertyDescriptor;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\npublic class MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME = \"generated.beanutils.MappedReferenceBean\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_BEAN_INTERNAL_NAME = \"generated/beanutils/MappedReferenceBean\";\n    private static final int CHUNK_BYTES = 4 * 1024 * 1024;\n\n    @Test\n    void reloadsMappedMethodThroughThreadContextClassLoaderAfterReferencesAreCleared() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            DescriptorScenario scenario = newDescriptorScenario();\n            forceReferencesToClear(scenario.methodRef, scenario.beanClassRef, scenario.classLoaderRef);\n\n            ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n            GeneratedBeanClassLoader reloadingClassLoader = new GeneratedBeanClassLoader();\n            try {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(reloadingClassLoader);\n\n                Method reloadedMethod = scenario.descriptor.getMappedReadMethod();\n\n                assertThat(reloadedMethod.getName()).isEqualTo(\"getValues\");\n                assertThat(reloadedMethod.getDeclaringClass().getClassLoader()).isSameAs(reloadingClassLoader);\n            } finally {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void triesFallbackClassLookupWhenThreadContextClassLoaderCannotReloadMappedMethodClass() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            DescriptorScenario scenario = newDescriptorScenario();\n            forceReferencesToClear(scenario.methodRef, scenario.beanClassRef, scenario.classLoaderRef);\n\n            ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n            try {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader());\n\n                assertThatThrownBy(() -> scenario.descriptor.getMappedReadMethod())\n                        .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                        .hasMessageContaining(\"could not be reconstructed\");\n            } finally {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static DescriptorScenario newDescriptorScenario()\n            throws ClassNotFoundException, IntrospectionException {\n        GeneratedBeanClassLoader classLoader = new GeneratedBeanClassLoader();\n        Class<?> beanClass = classLoader.loadClass(GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME);\n        MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor = new MappedPropertyDescriptor(\"values\", beanClass);\n        Method mappedReadMethod = descriptor.getMappedReadMethod();\n\n        return new DescriptorScenario(\n                descriptor,\n                new WeakReference<>(mappedReadMethod),\n                new WeakReference<>(beanClass),\n                new WeakReference<>(classLoader));\n    }\n\n    private static void forceReferencesToClear(WeakReference<?>... references) throws InterruptedException {\n        long deadline = System.nanoTime() + 30_000_000_000L;\n        while (!allReferencesCleared(references) && System.nanoTime() < deadline) {\n            System.gc();\n            List<byte[]> pressure = new ArrayList<>();\n            try {\n                int maxChunks = maximumPressureChunks();\n                for (int i = 0; i < maxChunks && !allReferencesCleared(references); i++) {\n                    pressure.add(new byte[CHUNK_BYTES]);\n                }\n            } catch (OutOfMemoryError expected) {\n                pressure.clear();\n                System.gc();\n            } finally {\n                pressure.clear();\n            }\n            System.gc();\n            Thread.sleep(100L);\n        }\n        assertThat(allReferencesCleared(references))\n                .as(\"method, generated class, and generated class loader references were cleared\")\n                .isTrue();\n    }\n\n    private static int maximumPressureChunks() {\n        long maxMemory = Runtime.getRuntime().maxMemory();\n        if (maxMemory == Long.MAX_VALUE) {\n            return 256;\n        }\n        return (int) Math.max(1L, Math.min(256L, maxMemory / CHUNK_BYTES));\n    }\n\n    private static boolean allReferencesCleared(WeakReference<?>... references) {\n        for (WeakReference<?> reference : references) {\n            if (reference.get() != null) {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] generatedBeanClassBytes() {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try {\n            DataOutputStream out = new DataOutputStream(bytes);\n            out.writeInt(0xCAFEBABE);\n            out.writeShort(0);\n            out.writeShort(52);\n            out.writeShort(17);\n            writeUtf8(out, GENERATED_BEAN_INTERNAL_NAME);\n            writeClass(out, 1);\n            writeUtf8(out, \"java/lang/Object\");\n            writeClass(out, 3);\n            writeUtf8(out, \"<init>\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"()V\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"Code\");\n            writeNameAndType(out, 5, 6);\n            writeMethodRef(out, 4, 8);\n            writeUtf8(out, \"getValues\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"(Ljava/lang/String;)Ljava/lang/String;\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"setValues\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"(Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;)V\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"SourceFile\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"MappedReferenceBean.java\");\n\n            out.writeShort(0x0021);\n            out.writeShort(2);\n            out.writeShort(4);\n            out.writeShort(0);\n            out.writeShort(0);\n            out.writeShort(3);\n            writeMethod(out, 5, 6, 1, 1, new byte[] {(byte) 0x2A, (byte) 0xB7, 0, 9, (byte) 0xB1});\n            writeMethod(out, 10, 11, 1, 2, new byte[] {(byte) 0x2B, (byte) 0xB0});\n            writeMethod(out, 12, 13, 0, 3, new byte[] {(byte) 0xB1});\n            out.writeShort(1);\n            out.writeShort(15);\n            out.writeInt(2);\n            out.writeShort(16);\n        } catch (IOException impossible) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(impossible);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static void writeUtf8(DataOutputStream out, String value) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(1);\n        out.writeUTF(value);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeClass(DataOutputStream out, int nameIndex) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(7);\n        out.writeShort(nameIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeNameAndType(DataOutputStream out, int nameIndex, int descriptorIndex) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(12);\n        out.writeShort(nameIndex);\n        out.writeShort(descriptorIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeMethodRef(DataOutputStream out, int classIndex, int nameAndTypeIndex) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(10);\n        out.writeShort(classIndex);\n        out.writeShort(nameAndTypeIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeMethod(\n            DataOutputStream out,\n            int nameIndex,\n            int descriptorIndex,\n            int maxStack,\n            int maxLocals,\n            byte[] code\n    ) throws IOException {\n        out.writeShort(0x0001);\n        out.writeShort(nameIndex);\n        out.writeShort(descriptorIndex);\n        out.writeShort(1);\n        out.writeShort(7);\n        out.writeInt(12 + code.length);\n        out.writeShort(maxStack);\n        out.writeShort(maxLocals);\n        out.writeInt(code.length);\n        out.write(code);\n        out.writeShort(0);\n        out.writeShort(0);\n    }\n\n    private static final class GeneratedBeanClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static final byte[] CLASS_BYTES = generatedBeanClassBytes();\n\n        private GeneratedBeanClassLoader() {\n            super(MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return defineClass(name, CLASS_BYTES, 0, CLASS_BYTES.length);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private RejectingClassLoader() {\n            super(MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class DescriptorScenario {\n        private final MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor;\n        private final WeakReference<Method> methodRef;\n        private final WeakReference<Class<?>> beanClassRef;\n        private final WeakReference<ClassLoader> classLoaderRef;\n\n        private DescriptorScenario(\n                MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor,\n                WeakReference<Method> methodRef,\n                WeakReference<Class<?>> beanClassRef,\n                WeakReference<ClassLoader> classLoaderRef\n        ) {\n            this.descriptor = descriptor;\n            this.methodRef = methodRef;\n            this.beanClassRef = beanClassRef;\n            this.classLoaderRef = classLoaderRef;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1832, "output": 7423, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44071, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777945340079, "responseId": "resp_0c214f9875a02c830169f94afc8ff481a1bc9354451683789d"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_QzcoFl0yI1IDJwC1hO4XGw7H|fc_0c214f9875a02c830169f94b3c9f4481a188952942abc3dd0c name=write args={"path": "tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage commons_beanutils.commons_beanutils_core;\n\nimport java.beans.IntrospectionException;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.DataOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.ref.WeakReference;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport org.apache.commons.beanutils.MappedPropertyDescriptor;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\npublic class MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME = \"generated.beanutils.MappedReferenceBean\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_BEAN_INTERNAL_NAME = \"generated/beanutils/MappedReferenceBean\";\n    private static final int CHUNK_BYTES = 4 * 1024 * 1024;\n\n    @Test\n    void reloadsMappedMethodThroughThreadContextClassLoaderAfterReferencesAreCleared() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            DescriptorScenario scenario = newDescriptorScenario();\n            forceReferencesToClear(scenario.methodRef, scenario.beanClassRef, scenario.classLoaderRef);\n\n            ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n            GeneratedBeanClassLoader reloadingClassLoader = new GeneratedBeanClassLoader();\n            try {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(reloadingClassLoader);\n\n                Method reloadedMethod = scenario.descriptor.getMappedReadMethod();\n\n                assertThat(reloadedMethod.getName()).isEqualTo(\"getValues\");\n                assertThat(reloadedMethod.getDeclaringClass().getClassLoader()).isSameAs(reloadingClassLoader);\n            } finally {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void triesFallbackClassLookupWhenThreadContextClassLoaderCannotReloadMappedMethodClass() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            DescriptorScenario scenario = newDescriptorScenario();\n            forceReferencesToClear(scenario.methodRef, scenario.beanClassRef, scenario.classLoaderRef);\n\n            ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n            try {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader());\n\n                assertThatThrownBy(() -> scenario.descriptor.getMappedReadMethod())\n                        .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                        .hasMessageContaining(\"could not be reconstructed\");\n            } finally {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static DescriptorScenario newDescriptorScenario()\n            throws ClassNotFoundException, IntrospectionException {\n        GeneratedBeanClassLoader classLoader = new GeneratedBeanClassLoader();\n        Class<?> beanClass = classLoader.loadClass(GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME);\n        MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor = new MappedPropertyDescriptor(\"values\", beanClass);\n        Method mappedReadMethod = descriptor.getMappedReadMethod();\n\n        return new DescriptorScenario(\n                descriptor,\n                new WeakReference<>(mappedReadMethod),\n                new WeakReference<>(beanClass),\n                new WeakReference<>(classLoader));\n    }\n\n    private static void forceReferencesToClear(WeakReference<?>... references) throws InterruptedException {\n        long deadline = System.nanoTime() + 30_000_000_000L;\n        while (!allReferencesCleared(references) && System.nanoTime() < deadline) {\n            System.gc();\n            List<byte[]> pressure = new ArrayList<>();\n            try {\n                int maxChunks = maximumPressureChunks();\n                for (int i = 0; i < maxChunks && !allReferencesCleared(references); i++) {\n                    pressure.add(new byte[CHUNK_BYTES]);\n                }\n            } catch (OutOfMemoryError expected) {\n                pressure.clear();\n                System.gc();\n            } finally {\n                pressure.clear();\n            }\n            System.gc();\n            Thread.sleep(100L);\n        }\n        assertThat(allReferencesCleared(references))\n                .as(\"method, generated class, and generated class loader references were cleared\")\n                .isTrue();\n    }\n\n    private static int maximumPressureChunks() {\n        long maxMemory = Runtime.getRuntime().maxMemory();\n        if (maxMemory == Long.MAX_VALUE) {\n            return 256;\n        }\n        return (int) Math.max(1L, Math.min(256L, maxMemory / CHUNK_BYTES));\n    }\n\n    private static boolean allReferencesCleared(WeakReference<?>... references) {\n        for (WeakReference<?> reference : references) {\n            if (reference.get() != null) {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] generatedBeanClassBytes() {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try {\n            DataOutputStream out = new DataOutputStream(bytes);\n            out.writeInt(0xCAFEBABE);\n            out.writeShort(0);\n            out.writeShort(52);\n            out.writeShort(17);\n            writeUtf8(out, GENERATED_BEAN_INTERNAL_NAME);\n            writeClass(out, 1);\n            writeUtf8(out, \"java/lang/Object\");\n            writeClass(out, 3);\n            writeUtf8(out, \"<init>\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"()V\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"Code\");\n            writeNameAndType(out, 5, 6);\n            writeMethodRef(out, 4, 8);\n            writeUtf8(out, \"getValues\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"(Ljava/lang/String;)Ljava/lang/String;\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"setValues\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"(Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;)V\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"SourceFile\");\n            writeUtf8(out, \"MappedReferenceBean.java\");\n\n            out.writeShort(0x0021);\n            out.writeShort(2);\n            out.writeShort(4);\n            out.writeShort(0);\n            out.writeShort(0);\n            out.writeShort(3);\n            writeMethod(out, 5, 6, 1, 1, new byte[] {(byte) 0x2A, (byte) 0xB7, 0, 9, (byte) 0xB1});\n            writeMethod(out, 10, 11, 1, 2, new byte[] {(byte) 0x2B, (byte) 0xB0});\n            writeMethod(out, 12, 13, 0, 3, new byte[] {(byte) 0xB1});\n            out.writeShort(1);\n            out.writeShort(15);\n            out.writeInt(2);\n            out.writeShort(16);\n        } catch (IOException impossible) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(impossible);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static void writeUtf8(DataOutputStream out, String value) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(1);\n        out.writeUTF(value);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeClass(DataOutputStream out, int nameIndex) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(7);\n        out.writeShort(nameIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeNameAndType(DataOutputStream out, int nameIndex, int descriptorIndex) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(12);\n        out.writeShort(nameIndex);\n        out.writeShort(descriptorIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeMethodRef(DataOutputStream out, int classIndex, int nameAndTypeIndex) throws IOException {\n        out.writeByte(10);\n        out.writeShort(classIndex);\n        out.writeShort(nameAndTypeIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeMethod(\n            DataOutputStream out,\n            int nameIndex,\n            int descriptorIndex,\n            int maxStack,\n            int maxLocals,\n            byte[] code\n    ) throws IOException {\n        out.writeShort(0x0001);\n        out.writeShort(nameIndex);\n        out.writeShort(descriptorIndex);\n        out.writeShort(1);\n        out.writeShort(7);\n        out.writeInt(12 + code.length);\n        out.writeShort(maxStack);\n        out.writeShort(maxLocals);\n        out.writeInt(code.length);\n        out.write(code);\n        out.writeShort(0);\n        out.writeShort(0);\n    }\n\n    private static final class GeneratedBeanClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static final byte[] CLASS_BYTES = generatedBeanClassBytes();\n\n        private GeneratedBeanClassLoader() {\n            super(MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return defineClass(name, CLASS_BYTES, 0, CLASS_BYTES.length);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private RejectingClassLoader() {\n            super(MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (GENERATED_BEAN_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class DescriptorScenario {\n        private final MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor;\n        private final WeakReference<Method> methodRef;\n        private final WeakReference<Class<?>> beanClassRef;\n        private final WeakReference<ClassLoader> classLoaderRef;\n\n        private DescriptorScenario(\n                MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor,\n                WeakReference<Method> methodRef,\n                WeakReference<Class<?>> beanClassRef,\n                WeakReference<ClassLoader> classLoaderRef\n        ) {\n            this.descriptor = descriptor;\n            this.methodRef = methodRef;\n            this.beanClassRef = beanClassRef;\n            this.classLoaderRef = classLoaderRef;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
